{"title":"State Bicycle Co. Launches Fully Aero, Fully Affordable, Sub-$3k Complete Carbon Road Bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/state-bicycle-co-launches-fully-aero-fully-affordable-sub-3k-complete-carbon-road-bike/","date":1780072316000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-hero.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" alt=\"Raw Black (Photos / State Bicycle Company)\" /></p>\n<p>A few months back, Arizona’s <a href=\"https://www.statebicycle.com/\" target=\"_blank\">State Bicycle Co</a>. launched a super affordable, fully aero, <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/the-sub-1400-fully-aero-state-bicycle-co-carbon-road-bike-frameset-is-now-available/\">carbon road frameset</a>. That frameset was a steal at under $1400, and it sold out quickly. Well, today, State expands its high-end road offerings beyond just a frameset with a new <a href=\"https://www.statebicycle.com/collections/state-bicycle-co-carbon-road-bike\" target=\"_blank\">Carbon Road Complete</a> using the same popular frameset.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-first-pic.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-first-pic.jpeg\" alt=\"State Bicycles Carbon Road Complete first pic\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-first-pic.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-first-pic-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-first-pic-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-first-pic-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-first-pic-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-first-pic-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Panda Pearl (Photos / State Bicycle Company)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Making their carbon platform accessible to more riders, the complete bikes will start at $2,799. This brings serious race-level carbon production bikes to a more affordable price range than we would typically see in this space.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-front-end.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-front-end.jpeg\" alt=\"State Bicycles Carbon Road Complete front end\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-front-end.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-front-end-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-front-end-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-front-end-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-front-end-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-front-end-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-brakes.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-brakes.jpeg\" alt=\"State Bicycles Carbon Road Complete rear brakes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-brakes.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-brakes-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-brakes-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-brakes-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-brakes-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-brakes-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>State’s new Carbon Road frame focuses on three key areas: aerodynamic efficiency for more speed and less effort, lightweight construction for easier climbing and handling, and practical usability for regular road cycling.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-blue-headtube.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-blue-headtube.jpeg\" alt=\"State Bicycles Carbon Road Complete blue headtube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-blue-headtube.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-blue-headtube-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-blue-headtube-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-blue-headtube-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-blue-headtube-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-blue-headtube-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Midnight Blue</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>The State Carbon Road Complete</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-desert-hour.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-desert-hour.jpeg\" alt=\"State Bicycles Carbon Road Complete desert hour\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-desert-hour.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-desert-hour-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-desert-hour-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-desert-hour-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-desert-hour-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-desert-hour-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The complete builds come in two different layups: Standard and SL. This gives riders frame options based on their performance needs and budget. The same frame design is currently being used in competitive racing and has <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/phil-gaimon-reclaims-mauna-kea-kom-calling-it-worst-40th-birthday-ever/\">proven capable on demanding climbs</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-drivetrain.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-drivetrain.jpeg\" alt=\"State Bicycles Carbon Road Complete drivetrain\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-drivetrain.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-drivetrain-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-drivetrain-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-drivetrain-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-drivetrain-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-drivetrain-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-cassette.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-cassette.jpeg\" alt=\"State Bicycles Carbon Road Complete rear cassette\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-cassette.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-cassette-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-cassette-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-cassette-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-cassette-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-rear-cassette-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So that means that riders get access to geometry and frame construction that’s been put to the test at high levels of performance. The Standard Complete bikes start at $2,800, while the SL Complete bikes save a pound of weight and start at $3,250.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Carbon Road Geometry</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Aero-Frameset-geo-2-e1772469498780.jpeg\"><img width=\"838\" height=\"606\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Aero-Frameset-geo-2-e1772469498780.jpeg\" alt=\"State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Aero-Frameset-geo-2-e1772469498780\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Aero-Frameset-geo-2-e1772469498780.jpeg 838w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Aero-Frameset-geo-2-e1772469498780-297x215.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Aero-Frameset-geo-2-e1772469498780-120x87.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Aero-Frameset-geo-2-e1772469498780-768x555.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Aero-Frameset-geo-1-e1772469537879.jpeg\"><img width=\"838\" height=\"356\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Aero-Frameset-geo-1-e1772469537879.jpeg\" alt=\"State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Aero-Frameset-geo-1-e1772469537879\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Aero-Frameset-geo-1-e1772469537879.jpeg 838w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Aero-Frameset-geo-1-e1772469537879-297x126.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Aero-Frameset-geo-1-e1772469537879-120x51.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Aero-Frameset-geo-1-e1772469537879-768x326.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-downtube-logo.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-downtube-logo.jpeg\" alt=\"State Bicycles Carbon Road Complete downtube logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-downtube-logo.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-downtube-logo-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-downtube-logo-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-downtube-logo-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-downtube-logo-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-downtube-logo-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>State Carbon Road Complete Retail &amp; Detail</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Retail: </h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Standard Complete: $2,800, </li>\n\n\n\n<li>SL Complete: $3,250 </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Frameset: $1,399</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Detail:</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Colors:\n<ul>\n<li>Standard frames: Panda Pearl and Midnight Blue </li>\n\n\n\n<li>SL frame: Raw Carbon</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tire clearance up to 32mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fully internal cable routing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>T47 threaded bottom bracket</li>\n\n\n\n<li>UDH-compatible derailleur hanger</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Standard and SL Frames</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM Rival E1 (2x) Drivetrain</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Enve Wheel Upgrade Available</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Weights: Size Medium<br />– Standard Layup: 18.5lb<br />– SL Layup: 17.5lb</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>So, if you’re a cyclist looking to transition to carbon but don’t want the typical premium pricing, the State Carbon Road Complete builds may be for you. It’s literally race-tested technology in a ready-to-ride package. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-sprint.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-sprint.jpeg\" alt=\"State Bicycles Carbon Road Complete sprint\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-sprint.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-sprint-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-sprint-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-sprint-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-sprint-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/State-Bicycles-Carbon-Road-Complete-sprint-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Get more details about the Carbon Road Complete, and check out all of the affordable bikes that State has to offer by hitting the link below.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=22249&amp;pw=293233&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statebicycle.com%2F\">StateBicycle.com</a></em></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/state-bicycle-co-launches-fully-aero-fully-affordable-sub-3k-complete-carbon-road-bike/\">State Bicycle Co. Launches Fully Aero, Fully Affordable, Sub-$3k Complete Carbon Road Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"f38e242dbf39597737f39eac6a95585dfcef0bdf5b254edd056a6d6eb42d4980","category":"Cycling"}